' with intimate descriptions of the predicaments, imaginations and activities of delta inhabitants. Conceptually, the collection develops 'delta life' as a metaphor for approaching continual and intersecting sociocultural, economic and material transformations more widely. The book revolves around questions of hydrosociality, volatility, rhythms and scale. It thereby yields insights into people's lives that conventional, hydrological approaches to deltas cannot provide.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDeltas. 0aEthnology. 0aWater-supply. 7aNATURE / Natural Resources.2bisacsh1 aCamargo, Alejandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Mark, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHorisberger, Nora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIvars, Benoit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrause, Franz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrause, Franz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLey, Lukas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichardson, Tanya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScaramelli, Caterina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimon, Sandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb2 aKnowledge Unlatchedefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831109